We recommended that Management:

Adopt policies and internal controls to monitor loan accommodations such that only those employees whose salaries do not fall below the prescribed amount of ₱5,000.00 after deducting the loan amortizations will be accommodated;

Direct those in charge of payroll preparation to exercise diligence in monitoring the monthly net take home pay of officials and employees to comply with the existing law;

Consider adopting the updated (2023) salary rates per DBM Local Budget Circular No. 149 dated January 10, 2023;

Implement remedial measures to rectify the situation of the forty personnel receiving a monthly net take home pay below the prescribed amount; and 

Strictly implement the mandatory monthly net take home pay of ₱5,000.00.

We recommended that Management:  
Through the Accounting Unit and Pharmacy to revisit and identify above variances amounting to ₱2,444,243.00 and ₱832,620.05 respectively by regularly reconciling their records;
Through the Purchasing unit to properly and fully accomplish PURCHASE ORDER (PO) details such as description of Medicines and its corresponding contents per box;
Through Inspector the and Property Officer to fully accomplish Inspection and Acceptance Report (IAR) with reference to actual date of receipt;
To submit Charge Invoices and Delivery Receipts from MAC Pharma & Medical Supplies amounting to ₱2,191,415.50;  
To submit Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) and its supporting documents in effecting adjustments on reconciled amounts.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare journal entries to reclassify tangible items, with costs below the capitalization threshold, that remain in the PPE account, in accordance with the illustrative entries outlined in Annex C of COA Circular No. 2024-06 dated March 14, 2024;
Instruct the General Services Office to consistently keep a separate monitoring of inventories and properties, with the necessary property records to maintain and reconcile regularly with the Accounting Department;
Review the entries of the PPE accounts recorded under the Special Education Fund and manually prepare a detailed schedule that includes all relevant information, such as acquisition cost, useful life, and accumulated depreciation.

We recommended that Management: 

Instruct the Accounting and Engineering Offices to reconcile its records starting from the CY 2023 year-end report and agree on the frequency of their succeeding regular reconciliation;

Upon adjustment of the costs of the completed projects, immediately reclassify to its respective PPE accounts;

Consider assigning project identification number, for more accurate assigning of costs to the project since there are projects with similar names which increases the chance for possible mis-posting of costs incurred.

