We recommended that Management:

Through the SEEDO manager to employ an effective and customized IT system tailored to the LGU’s distinct Economic Enterprises. Until the computerized system becomes available, SEEDO is advised to maintain financial records for each enterprise separately;

Through the Accounting unit to maintain separate records and prepare financial statements per economic enterprise in accordance with Section 110 of the NGAS for LGUs and the DBM Manual for financial self-sufficiency review of Local Economic Enterprises and;

Through the Accounting unit and SEEDO to reassess above approximated Net Income / (Net Loss) of the Economic Enterprises and submit Actual Financial Performance Report per each LGU’s economic venture.

We recommended to the Management to:

Through the Municipal Accountant, to demand in writing the immediate liquidation of fund transfer granted to various barangays by setting a specific timeline to be comply;
Verify the absence of any Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) for these projects. If proven to be none, provide a certification signed by both the Municipal Mayor and the Barangay Captain that no MOA was prepared relative to these projects;
